The paper discusses the emergence and importance of Mixed Reality (MR) technology within medical applications, which suggests a focus on Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) and Graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. The paper also applies text mining to a database of research papers, indicating a potential use of Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Augmented Reality (cs.AR) techniques. Finally, the paper aims to aid researchers and medical practitioners, indicating a possible connection to Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
